    <section id="social_media_safety">
        <h2><center>Social Media Safety<center></h2>
        <p>Social media platforms are a great way to connect with others, but they come with their own set of risks.
Avoid Sharing Location Details
Refrain from posting your real-time location, especially public check-ins,
as it may compromise your privacy and safety.

Verify Friend Requests
Be cautious when accepting friend or follow requests.
Scammers often create fake profiles to gain access to personal information.

Be Mindful of What You Post
Think twice before posting. Once something is online, it can be difficult
to fully remove, even if you delete it later.

Beware of Clickbait and Malicious Links
Avoid clicking on suspicious links or ads that seem too good to be true,
as they might lead to phishing websites or malware downloads.

Regularly Monitor Account Activity
Frequently check your account for unfamiliar logins or suspicious activity.
Report and secure your account immediately if you notice anything unusual. Here are some tips to stay safe:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Tip</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Limit Sharing Personal Information</td><td>Do not share sensitive personal information like your address, phone number, or financial details.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Privacy Settings</td><td>Adjust your privacy settings so only trusted friends can see your posts.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Beware of Strangers</td><td>Avoid interacting with people you don’t know. If you do, be cautious about the information you share.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vPlWDFtP0T0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </section>

    <section id="online_scams">
        <h2><center>Online Scams<center></h2>
        <p>Online scams can take many forms, from fraudulent emails to fake websites.<br>
Romance Scams.....<br>

Scammers may pose as potential romantic partners on dating websites or apps to gain your trust and eventually ask for money. Always verify their authenticity before engaging deeply.<br>
Job Offer Scams.....<br>

Be wary of unsolicited job offers promising high salaries with minimal effort. Scammers often request upfront payments for training or equipment.<br>
Lottery or Prize Scams.....<br>

You may receive messages claiming you’ve won a lottery or prize, but they require you to pay fees or share personal details. Genuine lotteries don’t ask for money upfront.<br>
Overpayment Scams.....<br>

Scammers might "overpay" for a product or service and request a refund of the excess. These payments are often fake, leaving you at a loss.<br>
Investment Scams.....<br>

Fraudsters offer fake investment opportunities with guaranteed high returns. Always research and verify the legitimacy of investment platforms. Stay alert to avoid falling victim:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Scam Type</th><th>Description</th><th>How to Avoid</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Phishing Emails</td><td>Fake emails that attempt to steal your personal details.</td><td>Never click on suspicious links and always verify the sender.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Fake Online Stores</td><td>Websites that offer products at unbelievably low prices to scam you.</td><td>Check reviews and ensure the site is secure (look for "https").</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tech Support Scams</td><td>Scammers pretending to be from tech support and asking for remote access to your device.</td><td>Never give remote access to strangers and contact official support for help.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/k8UVnkh8i0c" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </section>

    <section id="advantages_disadvantages">
        <h2><center>Advantages & Disadvantages<center></h2>
        <p>Every technology has its pros and cons. On the positive side, it provides accessibility to information and resources globally, enhances efficiency by automating tasks, and fosters connectivity through seamless communication. Technology also revolutionizes education by making it accessible to all and drives innovation in fields like healthcare and transportation. However, it comes with challenges such as privacy risks, where personal data can be misused, and digital addiction, which affects mental and physical health. Job displacement due to automation poses a threat to workers, while cyber threats like hacking and phishing increase vulnerability. Additionally, excessive use contributes to environmental issues like e-waste and energy consumption. Balancing its benefits and drawbacks is essential to ensure technology serves humanity responsibly. Here’s a breakdown:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Advantage</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Accessibility</td><td>The internet provides access to information and services from anywhere in the world.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Communication</td><td>Social media and messaging apps allow us to stay connected with loved ones.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Online Education</td><td>Online learning platforms make education accessible to people everywhere.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Disadvantage</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Privacy Risks</td><td>Personal data can be stolen or misused by hackers.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cyberbullying</td><td>The internet has become a platform for bullying and harassment.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Time Wastage</td><td>Excessive time on social media and other websites can reduce productivity and impact mental health.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xtQfV6COHbU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
