    <section id="tips_online_safety">
        <h2><center>Tips for Online Safety<center></h2>
        <p>To stay safe online, it is essential to follow key practices that protect your privacy and security. Start by using strong, complex passwords and enabling two-factor authentication for an extra layer of protection. Avoid clicking on suspicious links, as they can lead to phishing sites or malware. Regularly update your software to fix vulnerabilities and ensure your Wi-Fi network is secured with a strong password. Be cautious about sharing personal information online and always verify that websites are secure (look for "https" and a padlock symbol) before entering sensitive data. Adjust privacy settings on social media and apps to control what others can see. Educate yourself and your family about online threats to build awareness, and back up important data regularly to safeguard it in case of cyberattacks or device issues. By following these steps, you can navigate the digital world confidently and safely.<br>
Follow these practical tips to stay safe online:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Tip</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Use Strong Passwords</td><td>Create passwords that are hard to guess by mixing letters, numbers, and symbols.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Enable Two-Factor Authentication</td><td>Always use two-factor authentication wherever possible to add an extra layer of security.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Use Secure Websites</td><td>Look for "https" and a padlock symbol in the URL bar to ensure a website is secure.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Regularly Update Software</td><td>Keep your devices updated to protect them from vulnerabilities.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/aO858HyFbKI" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </section>

    <section id="cyber_attacks">
        <h2><center>Cyber Attacks<center></h2>
        <p>Cyber attacks are attempts to harm or break into systems, networks, or devices without permission. Common examples include phishing, where attackers trick people into sharing personal information, and ransomware, which locks your data until you pay money. Another example is a denial-of-service (DoS) attack, which floods a website with too much traffic so it stops working. To protect yourself, use strong passwords, turn on two-step verification, and keep your software updated. Avoid clicking on unknown links or emails, and always back up your important files. Being careful and staying informed can help keep you safe.
Cyber attacks come in various forms. Understanding the types can help you stay protected:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Attack Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Prevention</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Phishing</td><td>Attempts to steal personal information by pretending to be a trustworthy source.</td><td>Be cautious with emails and links from unknown sources.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ransomware</td><td>Malware that locks your data and demands a ransom to unlock it.</td><td>Backup data and avoid clicking on suspicious links.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Denial of Service (DoS)</td><td>An attack that floods a server with traffic, making it unavailable.</td><td>Use firewalls and intrusion detection systems to prevent attacks.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Dk-ZqQ-bfy4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </section>

    <section id="mindful_usage">
        <h2><center>Mindful Usage<center></h2>
        <p>Mindful technology usage involves being aware of how much time you spend on digital devices and how it affects your well-being. It’s important to set limits on screen time to avoid overuse and reduce the negative impact on your health. Taking regular breaks from screens helps prevent digital fatigue and gives your mind a chance to rest. Focus on meaningful online activities that enrich your life, instead of mindlessly scrolling. Being mindful also means being aware of the potential for digital addiction and making time for offline activities that help you stay balanced. By practicing mindful usage, you can maintain a healthy relationship with technology.Mindful technology usage helps maintain a healthy balance with digital devices:</p>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Tip</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Limit Screen Time</td><td>Set daily limits to reduce excessive screen time.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Take Breaks</td><td>Take regular breaks to avoid digital fatigue.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Focus on Quality</td><td>Engage in meaningful online activities rather than mindless scrolling.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Avoid Digital Addiction</td><td>Be aware of time spent online and its impact on your well-being.</td></tr>
        </table>
